'''Diogo de Macedo''' ([[Vila Nova de Gaia]], [[Portugal]], 22 November 1889 – [[Lisbon]], Portugal, 19 February 1959) was a [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] [[painter]], [[sculptor]], and writer.

==Sculpture==
Sculpted, among others, the busts of: 
*[[Antero de Quental]] ( 1929 )
*[[Sara Afonso]] ( 1927 )
*[[António Botto]] ( 1928 ) 
*[[Mário Eloy]] ( 1932 )
*some of the statues to the monumental fountain of Alameda ( 1940 - 1942)

